What is OOP?
OOP is stand for object oriented programming. which is paradigm /pattern /model of software development where it use objects and methods colbines 
to develop efficient softwares and write modular, resuable, maintainable code and softwares rather than only functions and logic.

Key Principles of OOP / Types of OOP:
There are 4 main types of OOP's i.e. Encapsulation, Abstraction, inheritance and polymorphism.
